{"query_text":"
-- regarding BUYERS
-- Example question:
-- Which countries have the best buyers ? 
--   This answer would allow you to adapt your products to the style of the people from there

---------------------------------------------

-- Mininmum number of Products Bought to be considered a top buyer
DECLARE ?minProductsBought AS INTEGER = 10


SELECT
  country
column59: \n  \n  SUM(CASE gender WHEN \"F\" THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as femaleBuyers
column60:
-- Stats for top Buyers

  SUM(CASE WHEN productsBought >= ?minProductsBought THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) nbTopBuyers
column61: \n  SUM(CASE WHEN productsBought >= ?minProductsBought THEN productsBought ELSE 0 END) topTotalProductsBought
column62: \n  SUM(CASE WHEN productsBought >= ?minProductsBought THEN productsWished ELSE 0 END) topTotalProductsWished
column63: \n  SUM(CASE WHEN productsBought >= ?minProductsBought THEN socialproductsliked ELSE 0 END) topTotalProductsLiked
column64: \n  SUM(CASE WHEN productsBought >= ?minProductsBought THEN socialnbfollowers ELSE 0 END) topFollowersCount
column65: \n  SUM(CASE WHEN productsBought >= ?minProductsBought THEN socialnbfollows ELSE 0 END) topFollowingCount
column66: \n  SUM(CASE WHEN productsBought >= ?minProductsBought THEN dayssincelastlogin ELSE 0 END) topTotalDaysSinceLastLogin
column67:
SUM(CASE WHEN (productsBought >= ?minProductsBought AND gender = "F") THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as topFemaleBuyers

FROM `6m_0k_99k_users_dataset_public`
WHERE productsBought > 0  -- filter to only successful Buyers (not prospecting Buyers)


GROUP BY country

) AS precomputedStats

--WHERE (nbtopBuyers > 0)
WHERE (nbbuyers > 0)
--ORDER BY totalproductsBought DESC
ORDER BY nbtopBuyers DESC
column74: description:"User's country (written in french). See also the column \"Country Code\" if you prefer an ISO identifier."
